<subSubSection id="C331F4EFFFD81D4250A7FD51FDACFB4C" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B94A764FFD81D4250A7FD51FC90FB8C" blockId="6.[170,795,698,1235]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD81D4250A7FD51FCCAFD4C" bold="true" box="[170,439,698,723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum dark brown in the centre, clearing towards borders, margins and angles pale yellow; elytra dark brown, with yellowish to lightbrown apical patch; males: femur swollen, wider medially, with inconspicuous rounded ventral tooth; ventrite VIII with a short, oblique ridge near left margin; aedeagus with right prolongation of tegmen broadly projected dorsally; left setiferous prolongation elongate,wide,with short apical setae; females: abdominal ventrite VII short, wide,lateral margins arched,posterior angles emarginat- ed, posterior margin straight.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B94A764FFD81D4250DDFBF1FDACFB4C" blockId="6.[170,795,698,1235]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Males differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BDCE7FFD81D425183FBF1FF5EFBAC" authorityName="Brancucci" authorityYear="1981" box="[398,547,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belemensis">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD81D425183FBF1FF5EFBAC" box="[398,547,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">M. belemensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence in the latter of fore femur with an inconspicuous rounded ventral tooth, distal margins of abdominal ventrite VII wider and aedeagus with left paramere present. Distal margin of ventrite VII of females straight (notched in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BDCE7FFD81D42529AFB71FDB9FB4C" authorityName="Brancucci" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belemensis">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD81D42529AFB71FDB9FB4C" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">M.belemensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C331F4EFFFD81D435368FF31FCC0FB6C" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B94A764FFD81D425368FF31F923FDAC" blockId="6.[869,1494,218,563]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD81D425368FF31F921FF6C" bold="true" box="[869,1116,218,243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Description: Length:</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CD30A81FFD81D425465FF31F991FF6C" box="[1128,1260,218,243]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.6">5.6-6.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD81D4254F6FF31F8F2FF6C" bold="true" box="[1275,1423,218,243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Colouration:</emphasis>
Head predominantly black, clypeus dark brown; antennae dark brown, testaceous on antennomeres I-III; labium and maxillae light brown, palpomeres light brown to testaceous; mandibles light brown at apex and pale yellow at base; pronotum dark brown at centre, clearing towards borders, margins and angles pale yellow; elytra dark brown with a yellowish to light-brown apical patch; wings dark brown; thorax and abdomen light brown; legs pale yellow to light brown, darker at apex of femora, tibiae and tarsi (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD81D425418FDF1F92EFDAC" box="[1045,1107,538,563]" captionStart="Figures 1-6" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1356,206,2041]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[151,1360,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1-6:Dorsal habitus ofMacromalthinus species.(1) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(2)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(3)M.orapuensis sp.nov.(4) M.piceiventrissp.nov. (5) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(6)M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384149/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B94A764FFD81D435368FDB1FCBEFC8C" blockId="6.[869,1494,602,1235]" lastBlockId="7.[94,719,218,787]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD81D425368FDB1FECFFDEC" bold="true" box="[869,946,602,627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Males:</emphasis>
Head large, transverse, 1.2 times wider than pronotum; temples elongate, strongly tapering posteriorly; vertex and frons concave. Eyes bulging, oblong, prominent. Antennae filiform,flattened dorso-ventrally, densely covered with thin setae; antennomere I wide, II very short,III 0.6 times shorter than I, IV and V nearly as long as I, VI slightly longer than the following ones, progressively decreasing in length apically. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD81D425527FCD1F81AFCCC" box="[1322,1383,826,851]" captionStart="Figures 7-12" captionStartId="4.[869,937,1217,1242]" captionTargetBox="[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-697@4.[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 7-12: Pronotum of Macromalthinus species. (7) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (8) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (9) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (10) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (11) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (12) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384151/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) nearly as long as wide; anterior margin slightly arched,lateral margins slightly constricted near anterior angles, sinuate and convergent from anterior half; pronotal surface elevated antero-medially and near posterior angles, forming two lateral shallow grooves, parallel lateral margins, convergent posteriorly. Elytra short, rugulose, densely covered with short and thin setae;sutures dehiscent from posteri- or half; apex slightly swollen dorsally. Fore femur (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD81D425588FBD1F8B2FBCC" box="[1413,1487,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figures 13-18" captionStartId="5.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[97,1416,991,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-354@5.[94,1417,986,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 13-18: Fore femur of Macromalthinus species. (13) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (14) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov.(15) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(16) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(17) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(18) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384153/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) swollen, wider medially, with inconspicuous rounded ventral tooth; femora, tibiae and tarsomeres increasing in length from fore to hind legs; tarsal claws simple, not toothed. Abdominal tergites and sternites sclerotized; ventrites densely covered with long thin setae; glandular pores not prominent; distal margin of ventrite VI entire, not notched, slightly membranous; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD91D435276FEF1FFB5FEAC" box="[635,712,282,307]" captionStart="Figures 19-24" captionStartId="6.[170,238,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[172,1491,1272,2042]" captionTargetId="figure-506@6.[170,1493,1269,2044]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 19-24:Ventrite VII of males of Macromalthinus species.(19) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(20) M.luteoapicalis sp.nov.(21)M. orapuensis sp.nov.(22) M.piceiventris sp.nov.(23) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(24) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384156/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) H-shaped,lateral margins sinuous,with a broad membranous area anteriorly and a wide posterior notch; ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD91D43509FFE91FD9CFE0C" box="[146,225,378,403]" captionStart="Figures 25-30" captionStartId="7.[794,862,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[798,1414,205,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-491@7.[794,1418,204,1980]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 25-30: Ventrite VIII of males of Macromalthinus species. (25) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (26) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (27) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(28)M.piceiventrissp.nov.(29) M.quadratithoraxsp.nov.(30) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384158/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical, irregularly oblong, strongly convex; a short,oblique ridge near left margin.Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD91D435068FE51FDCDFE4C" box="[101,176,442,467]" captionStart="Figures 31-36" captionStartId="8.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1491,674,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-183@8.[170,1493,670,2012]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 31-36: Aedeagus of Macromalthinus species. (31) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (32) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (33) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (34) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(35) M. quadratithorax sp.nov.(36) M. xerophilus sp.nov. Abbreviations:pt = prolongation of tegmen, sp = setiferous prolongation,rp = right paramere, lp = left paramere,ml = median lobe.Scale bars:0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384160/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with right prolongation of tegmen broadly projected dorsally, without apophysis on dorsal surface; left setiferous prolongation elongate, wide, with short apical setae; right paramere elongate, straight, apex acute, slightly curved; left paramere elongate, narrow, flat, apex rounded; median lobe straight, broad, apex membranous. 
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD91D4350AEFD91FC92FD0C" bold="true" box="[163,495,634,659]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Measurements of 
<typeStatus id="549019C6FFD91D435170FD91FC91FD0C" box="[381,492,634,659]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
TL: 6.0; AL: 4.8; OL: 0.51; HW: 1.12; IOW: 0.57; IAW: 0.20; PL: 0.86; PW: 0.93; EL: 1.8; EW: 1.24. 
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD91D4350F5FD51FF27FD4C" bold="true" box="[248,602,698,723]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Length of each antennomere:</emphasis>
aI: 0.3; aII: 0.18; aIII: 0.30; aIV: 0.43; aV: 0.45; aVI: 0.47; aVII: 0.47; aVIII: 0.48; aIX: 0.48; aX: 0.43; aXI: 0.46.
</paragraph>
