<paragraph id="8B94A764FFD91D435053FCD1FCC0FB6C" blockId="7.[94,719,826,1267]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD91D435053FCD1FDC6FCCC" bold="true" box="[94,187,826,851]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Female:</emphasis>
Similar to males; eyes smaller, less prominent; fore femora slender, without intumescence or tooth; ventrite VI entire, not notched posteriorly; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD91D435068FC71FDCAFC2C" box="[101,183,922,947]" captionStart="Figures 37-42" captionStartId="9.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[94,1414,1424,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-592@9.[94,1417,1420,2044]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 37-42:VentriteVII offemales ofMacromalthinusspecies.(37) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(38)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(39) M.orapuensissp.nov.(40)M.piceiventris sp.nov.(41) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(42) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384162/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
) short, wide, lateral margins arched, anterior angles emarginated, posterior margin straight; coxites (
<figureCitation id="1310BBE1FFD91D435068FC31FDC9FC6C" box="[101,180,986,1011]" captionStart="Figures 43-48" captionStartId="10.[869,937,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[873,1490,1055,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-666@10.[869,1493,1054,1980]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 43-48: Coxites of Macromalthinus species. (43) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (44) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (45) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (46) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (47) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (48) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384164/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
) with base elongate, slender, apex very short, with a short, broad projection behind styles bearing few thin setae; styles short, slightly wider apically, bearing some setae of different thicknesses. 
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFD91D4351F0FBD1FCB9FBEC" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
